Vice President Biden will be traveling to Kyiv, Ukraine, to meet with government leaders and members of civil society on April 22nd. The purpose of the trip is to show strong support for a united, democratic Ukraine that can make its own choices about its future. The Vice President will discuss efforts to stabilize and strengthen Ukraine's economy, as well as assist with constitutional reform, decentralization, anti-corruption efforts, and the upcoming presidential elections. He will also address the situation in eastern Ukraine, where pro-Russian separatists are destabilizing the country with the support of Moscow. Energy security and deepening the partnership between the United States and Ukraine will also be topics of discussion.